<br>
Feel free to give as muc feedback as possible.<br>
<br>
_________________________________<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Under the Night &amp; An Affirming Flame:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Beka walked into the room she’d discovered as Harper’s new quarters. The room was large and bare, except for the beige bed against the far wall. Looking around, Beka would’ve believed she was in one of the ship’s many machine shops she’d seen while walking down the deck. She knew that, in no time, the room would be filled with dozens of Harper’s little projects. She was glad that now he had the freedom to create all of the little knickknacks he used to babble on about. The Maru didn’t exactly allow for experimentation. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Hey, Boss, ya wanna move so I can get in?” asked Harper. She hadn’t heard him walk in. He was carrying a large box filled with his stuff from the Maru. She saw one of his many brightly colored Hawaiian shirts draping over the side. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Sorry, Harper,” she said, stepping aside. Grinning, he walked in, setting the box down on the floor. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Found your own place yet?” he asked, beginning to sort through the junk in the box. Beka had never noticed before, but now it was painfully obvious how little Harper really had. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Beka shrugged, still looking around the room. “The rooms on Deck 15 are nice. They probably belonged to the old officers. Though they’re not as spacious as this.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Yeah, cool, isn’t it? Rommie told me her old engineer used to live in a room like this,” Harper said, hardly able to contain the excitement in his voice. Beka had never seen him so happy before, like he’d found a new toy to play with. “Now I can work and sleep in the same place.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Rommie, huh?” Beka said, raising an eyebrow. “You two on a first name basis?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“It’s not like she has a last name, Beka,” he said, looking away sheepishly. She swore she saw him blush. “Besides, we might as well get to know her. We will be staying for a while.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Yeah, I guess we are,” Beka said, sighing as she sat on Harper’s bed. Harper stopped sorting through his things. Being together for so long, he’d developed a sixth sense about Beka’s moods and feelings. He sat next to her, leaning his elbows on his knees. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“You’re not so sure about this, are you?” he said, more as a statement then a question. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“No, I’m not,” she said. “I mean, restoring the Commonwealth? Come on, who does he think he is?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Captain Dylan Hunt of the High Guard?” Harper said. Beka glared at her engineer. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Thank you, Harper.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Don’t mention it,” he said. “Look, he said we’re free to go at any time. Give it a chance, Bek. What’s the worst that could happen?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Do you really have to ask?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Okay, since I happen to be just as suspicious and paranoid as you, here’s what I’m gonna do. You know those override codes I installed in Andromeda’s system so we could take over the ship?<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Yeah?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Well, I have to erase them so that Dylan had complete control of the ship.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Great, then he’ll have all the power over us. He’ll have us bowing to his every whim and fancy,” Beka said. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Would you calm down? Anyway, because I don’t totally trust the guy, I’ll only erase a few of the codes. That way, if he goes all psycho on us, we can get away free and easy,” he said.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“You’d do that?” she asked.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Beka, I’m always working for you. Just ‘cause we’re Dylan’s new crew doesn’t change that. Any time you wanna go, just say the word and I’ll be with you,” he said, smiling. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I couldn’t imagine leaving without you,” she said, placing an arm around his shoulders, giving him a tight squeeze. “Wanna come find me a room?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Sure! I’m almost done unpacking anyway,” he said, laughing. Beka laughed along with him. They left the practically empty room, ready to face the coming adventure; together. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>To Loose the Fateful Lightning:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“You made an android?” Beka asked, steering the Maru toward the escape pods floating around. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I needed something to do,” Harper said, standing next to the pilot’s chair.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“And you thought making a woman was the best way to pass the time?” she asked. Harper frowned. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“What’re you getting at, Beka?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“What were you expecting when you made her?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Harper paused. “Nothing.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Nothing? You mean you didn’t expect Rommie to be grateful for having an avatar and wanting to show you her appreciation?” she asked. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“No,” Harper lied.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Harper!”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Okay, okay, maybe it was for me! So sue me!” he shouted. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Don’t get angry at me for this. You’re the one setting yourself up for rejection,” Beka countered, her voice remaining calm.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I don’t know what you’re talking about,” Harper grumbled. Beka turned to face him, seeing the hurt already in his eyes.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Harper, I just don’t want you to get hurt,” she said, touching his arm. “I know she’s sentient now, but that doesn’t make her anymore available.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I know what I’m doing, Beka,” he said. She smiled sadly. Harper had already fallen hopelessly in love with Andromeda and there was nothing she could do to protect him. She turned back to the controls.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Yeah, I know you do.”<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>D-Minus Zero:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
Beka entered the med-deck after her conversation with Dylan. Harper lay on the bed, a blanket draped over him courtesy of Trance after he’d fallen asleep. He still looked like hell. His skin was sickly and pale and she could see a slight tremor in his body appear sporadically. Trance was saying nothing but good things about his recovery, but Beka always over worried when it came to Harper. She slid a chair over to the bed. Without saying a word, Harper’s eyes fluttered open. He looked at Beka, his eyes partially glazed over from sleep. When his focus came back, Harper smiled.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Hey, Boss,” he said, recalling a similar beginning to a conversation with Dylan.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Hey,” she said. “How do you feel?”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Like crap, but that’s better than I felt an hour ago,” he said. She saw his smile fade. Guilt set into his face. “I’m sorry, Beka.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“For what?” she asked, already knowing the reason.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I shouldn’t have made the FMS. Dylan wouldn’t have been able to—” he started. Beka placed a finger over his mouth, stopping him.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Shut up,” she said. Taking her finger away, Harper stayed quiet. “You did your job, Harper. And if you hadn’t made the FMS, I don’t think any of us would be here right now.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“But, Dylan—”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Dylan was trying to save us and I was being stupid. You didn’t do anything wrong,” she said.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I would’ve gone with you,” he whispered. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“I know,” she said, ruffling his hair. She could see that the conversation was tiring him. She began to slowly stroke his hair, humming gently. “Go to sleep, Harper. You’ve had a long day.”<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
“Okay,” he said, his voice trailing off. She watched his eyes close and his breathing even out into a slow, calm rhythm. He was asleep. She stayed by his side until he woke up the next morning.<br>
<br>
